#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:2
msgid "return - stop the current inner function"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:7
msgid "return [N]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:12
msgid "Description"
msgstr "描述"

#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:14
msgid ""
":program:`return` halts a currently running function. The exit status is set "
"to *N* if it is given. If :program:`return` is invoked outside of a function "
"or dot script it is equivalent to exit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:18
msgid ""
"It is often added inside of a conditional block such as an :doc:`if <if>` "
"statement or a :doc:`switch <switch>` statement to conditionally stop the "
"executing function and return to the caller; it can also be used to specify "
"the exit status of a function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:20
msgid ""
"If at the top level of a script, it exits with the given status, like :doc:"
"`exit <exit>`. If at the top level in an interactive session, it will set :"
"envvar:`status`, but not exit the shell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:23
msgid "The **-h** or **--help** option displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:26
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:28
msgid "An implementation of the false command as a fish function: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/return.rst:31
msgid ""
"function false\n"
"    return 1\n"
"end"
msgstr ""
